{"lemma":"قَزِّ","slug":"قَزِّ","root":"ق.ز.ز","root_slug":"ق-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2272","n35568","n35569","n35570","n35571"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"silk, silkware"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abhor, to shrink in the soul from, to detest, to loathe"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic קָזָא / קָאזָא (qāzzā, “floss silk, cotton-seed”) from Middle Persian [script needed] (kač) (New Persian کژ (kaž)), which has also been borrowed directly as خَزّ (ḵazz). See the New Persian entry for more."},"ipa":["/qazz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2272","headword_ar":"قز","root":"brsm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":":) or a kind thereof: (S in that art.:) or that whereof"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrysm","text_ar":"ابريسم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made: (Lth, Az, Msb, TA, all in that art.:) [medicinal properties are ascribed to it: it is said that]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is exhilarating, warming to the body, moderate in temperament, and strengthening to the sight when used as a collyrium:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the word is arabicized, (S, Msb, K, [but in the last it is said, after the explanation of the meaning, “or it is arabicized,”]) from [the Persian]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abry$m","text_ar":"ابريشم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboriy$amo","text_ar":"اَبْرِيشَمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and is perfectly decl., even if used as a proper name, in the manner of a surname, because it was arabicized in its indeterminate state, not like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isoHaAqu","text_ar":"اـِسْحَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., which were arabicized in their determinate state, and are not used by the Arabs indeterminately. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n35568","headword_ar":"قَزَّ","root":"qz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [sec. pers., app.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qazuzota","text_ar":"قَزُزْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qazaAzapN","text_ar":"قَزَازَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He felt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a sense of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was moved with, shame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pudency; his soul shrank from foul things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqz~z","text_ar":"تقزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was scrupulous in shunning, or avoiding, unclean things, or impurities;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed himself far from such things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quz~N","text_ar":"قُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~a","text_ar":"قَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaz~uzN","text_ar":"تَقَزُّزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~a mina Ald~anasi","text_ar":"قَزَّ مِنَ الدَّنَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quz~N","text_ar":"قُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed himself far from what was unclean."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~ato nafosiY Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"قَزَّتْ نَفْسِى عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~atohu","text_ar":"قَزَّتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with and without a prep., (M, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~N","text_ar":"قَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My soul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind, refused the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rejected it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, * TA;) a meaning said by IKtt to be of the dial. of El-Yemen: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it loathed the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which latter is the more common signification: (M, TA:) and [in like manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqz~z","text_ar":"تقزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not eat the thing, nor drink it, willingly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) end"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqz~z","text_ar":"تقزّز","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoli AlD~ab~i wagayorihi","text_ar":"اَكْلِ الضَّبِّ وَغَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he loathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shunned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2520},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided, the eating of the lizard called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Mgh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n35569","headword_ar":"قَزٌّ","root":"qz","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing, that is to be loathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shunned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avoided, for its uncleanness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in food; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quz~u","text_ar":"قُزُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qazaAzapN","text_ar":"قَزَازَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) See also 1.       -A2-  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who feels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has a sense of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is moved with, shame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pudency; whose soul shrinks from foul things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) and, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quz~N","text_ar":"قُزٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiz~N","text_ar":"قِزٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrupulous in shunning, or avoiding, unclean things, or impurities;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who removes himself far from such things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not eat nor drink a thing willingly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and the same three epithets, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qazazN","text_ar":"قَزَزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quz~aAzN","text_ar":"قُزَّازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,) a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well-bred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"polite,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZariyfN","text_ar":"ظَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who guards against vices or faults, and shuns acts of disobedience and afflictions, not through pride:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~apN","text_ar":"قَزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quz~apN","text_ar":"قُزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiz~apN","text_ar":"قِزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K: *) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~N","text_ar":"قَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqiz~aA='u","text_ar":"اَقِزَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is anomalous. (M, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboriysamN","text_ar":"اـِبْرِيسَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Silk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raw silk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that whereof"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrysm","text_ar":"ابريسم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is made;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Az, Msb, TA;) wherefore some say, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qz~","text_ar":"قزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abrysm","text_ar":"ابريسم"},{"kind":"text","text":"are like wheat and flour: (Msb:) a Persian word, [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qazo","text_ar":"قَزْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M, TA,) arabicized: (S, M, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quzuwzN","text_ar":"قُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwdu Alqaz~i","text_ar":"دُودُ القَزِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The silk-worm."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K","IAar","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n35570","headword_ar":"قُزٌّ","root":"qz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~N","text_ar":"قَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the first in three places, and the second in two."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n35571","headword_ar":"قِزٌّ","root":"qz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaz~N","text_ar":"قَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the first in three places, and the second in two."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}